.:: Puzzle 1x4-Level-4-6::.
4 different games are played: go, monopoly, canasta, domino
1. the person playing monopoly is on the far right##1
2. the person playing monopoly is on the left or right of the person playing domino##3
3. the person playing canasta is in an odd position##4

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1     |     2     |  3   |    4    |
| Game   | canasta | go | domino | monopoly |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 1x4-Level-4-7::.
The people have 4 different hobbies: collecting, rock-climbing, traveling, video-games
1. the person who's hobby is collecting is on the left or right of the person who's hobby is video-games##3
2. the person who's hobby is video-games is in an odd position##4
3. the person who's hobby is traveling is between the person who's hobby is collecting and the person who's hobby is rock-climbing##2

.:: Answer ::.
|       |   1    |    2    |      3      |     4      |
| Hobby   | video-games | collecting | traveling | rock-climbing |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 1x4-Level-4-8::.
City: colone, nizza, new-york, san-francisco
1. the person traveling to nizza is in an even position##4
2. the person traveling to san-francisco is on the right of the person traveling to nizza##1
3. the person traveling to colone is on the right of the person traveling to san-francisco##1

.:: Answer ::.
|       |     1     |      2       |     3      |  4   |
| City   | new-york | nizza | san-francisco | colone |

